        },
        {
          "text": "; the second note‚Äôs frequency is 1.06√ó the first "
        },
        {
          "type": "note",
          "id": "bb7a75e3-6b19-42fc-adf2-548329a28f9a",
          "noteStr": "C#4",
          "editing": false,
          "children": [
            {
              "text": ""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " (‚Äú#‚Äù means raise a semitone, ‚Äúb‚Äù means lower), the third is 1.06√ó the second "
        },
        {
          "type": "note",
          "id": "bb7a75e3-6b19-42fc-adf2-548329a28f9a",
          "noteStr": "D4",
          "editing": false,
          "children": [
            {
              "text": ""
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": ", and so on, giving 12 notes (1.06 is approximate; search ‚Äú12-tone equal temperament‚Äù if curious). The distance between two pitches is called an ‚Äúinterval‚Äù; the smallest interval in modern music is a ‚Äúsemitone‚Äù; its frequency ratio is ~1.06. A ‚Äúwhole tone‚Äù is 1.06√ó1.06. No need to memorize the numbers‚Äîjust grasp the idea."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
