          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Feeling dizzy? That‚Äôs normal‚Äîdizziness means knowledge is swirling in your brain. If anything is unclear, ask the AI helper at the top ü§ñ"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Continuing the 1.06√ó calculation until the last note‚Äôs frequency is double the first (the ‚Äúoctave‚Äù) yields the 12 standard pitches of modern music: C, C#, D, D#, E, F, F#, G, G#, A, A#, B. ‚Äú#‚Äù is sharp, raising a note by a semitone; E-F is already defined as a semitone (many such ‚Äúrules‚Äù exist in music‚Äîno need to over-think). Listen to these 12 notes:"
