    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "But these are all letter names ABCD; how do they relate to the 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 we started with?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Note names are "
        },
        {
          "text": "fixed",
          "bold": true
        },
        {
          "text": " labels for individual pitches; 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 is a scale, a set of "
        },
        {
          "text": "relationships",
          "bold": true
        },
        {
          "text": "‚Äîit‚Äôs dynamic. When you hum 1 2 3 4 5 6 7, no matter which pitch you start on, it feels ‚Äúthe same‚Äù because "
        },
        {
          "text": "a scale is about the intervals between notes",
          "bold": true
        },
        {
          "text": ". As long as the interval pattern is identical, you‚Äôre singing the same scale; you can let 1 be C, D, or anything you like."
        }
