    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "You should also realize that the absolute pitch of a melody doesn‚Äôt matter; what matters is the ‚Äúintervals‚Äù. As long as the intervals are identical, it sounds similar. Scale degrees have specific interval relationships, proven by predecessors to be harmonious and pleasant."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "But scales aren‚Äôt limited to ‚Äú1 2 3 4 5 6 7‚Äù. Pleasant pitch sets are countless. The Chinese-sounding ‚Äúpentatonic scale‚Äù is ‚Äú1 2 3 5 6‚Äù. Try clicking these notes at will "
        },
        {
